  <static seed="96" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionSubtractionWordProblems50.pg">
    <statement><p>Tammy and Katherine are sharing a pizza. Tammy ate <m>{{\frac{3}{8}}}</m> of the pizza, and Katherine ate <m>{{\frac{2}{9}}}</m> of the pizza. How much more pizza did Tammy eat than Katherine?</p>
<p>Tammy ate <fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/> more of the pizza than Katherine ate.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{11}{72}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To find the difference of two numbers, we use subtraction:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{3}{8}}} - {{\frac{2}{9}}} 
      \amp = \frac{3 \cdot 9}{8 \cdot 9}-\frac{2 \cdot 8}{9 \cdot 8} \\
      \amp = \frac{27}{72} - \frac{16}{72} \\
      \amp = \frac{27-16}{72} \\
      
      \amp = {{\frac{11}{72}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Tammy ate <m>{{\frac{11}{72}}}</m> more of the pizza than Katherine ate.</p>
</solution>
